{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:52:50.869Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1778899970869_1","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-020@20260515T214233Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** gemini-3-flash-preview\n**Date:** 2026-05-16\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `promptclaw/pal_agent.py`\n- `tests/test_pal_agent.py`\n- `progress.md`\n- `sdp/notifications.log`\n- `sdp/run-log.md`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of `verify_pal_artifact_redaction` in `promptclaw/pal_agent.py` correctly identifies several secret patterns including:\n- `PAL_SSH_KEY` assignments (using `PAL_SSH_KEY\\s*[=:]\\s*\\S`)\n- PEM private key blocks\n- GitHub, OpenAI, Slack, and AWS tokens/IDs\n\nThe verifier recursively scans all files in the provided `run_root` and returns a structured `PALArtifactRedactionVerification` object indicating whether any findings were found.\n\n## Completeness\nThe task required failing artifacts containing `PAL_SSH_KEY` or token-like values. The implementation covers a broad range of token shapes (GitHub, OpenAI, Slack, AWS) and handles the specific case of `PAL_SSH_KEY` assignments while avoiding false positives on simple mentions (as demonstrated in tests).\n\n## Consistency\nThe code uses standard Python dataclasses and regex patterns, following the established style in `promptclaw/pal_agent.py`. The types `PALSecretFinding` and `PALArtifactRedactionVerification` are well-structured and provide a dictionary representation for easy export.\n\n## Security\nThe tool itself is designed to improve security by identifying leaked secrets in workflow artifacts. The regexes used are conservative enough to catch most leaks while allowing non-secret mentions.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is clean, well-typed, and includes error handling for file reading (using `errors=\"replace\"` to avoid decoding failures). A comprehensive test case `test_pal_artifact_redaction_verifier_flags_secret_leakage` was added and passes.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] No issues found.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe verifier is implemented as a standalone utility. Future tasks should integrate this into the main PAL workflow or `verify_pal_workflow_artifacts` to ensure automatic secret checking of all runs.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-020@20260515t214233z-verify.md"}}
